          <h2 class="page-header">Context</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 content">
        <p>Most farmers in sub-Saharan Africa practice rain-fed agriculture. Not enough rain means plants don’t produce a harvest while too much rain can kill
          growing crops. To mitigate adverse effects of heavy rainfall or drought on crop yield, weather index insurance is an innovative risk management solution,
          mostly intended to insure smallholders’ farmers against climate risk. The weather index insurance is based on an event’s probability to trigger a payout
          from independent meteorological data, which both farmer and insurer have access to
        </p>
        <p>Yet, the poor rain gauge network in sub-Saharan Africa prevents a proper risk assessment and an accurate insurance design. If the spatial and temporal
          variability of rainfall is not accurately estimated, only areas covered by a dense rain gauge network with long histories can benefit from insurance
          coverage.
        </p>
      </div>
