      <div class="col-md-6 content">
        <p>Hadley Innovation proposes to overcome the challenge of missing information by simulating realistic rainfall data, away from gauge stations. Known as    <em>stochastic modeling of space-time rainfall field, </em>our simulator accounts for the spatial and temporal variability of rainfall distribution. The
          model is inspired from state-of-the-art in geostatistics
        </p>
        <p>From ground observations measurements, statistical analysis of rainfall distribution is first achieved to infer input parameters in our rainfall simulator.
          In output, relevant information is generated at locations with no previous measurements, or where only short data series are available. Synthetic rainfall
          data intend to improve weather index design and to lower premiums, making insurance more affordable.
        </p>
